<subSubSection lastPageId="37" lastPageNumber="90" pageId="36" pageNumber="89" type="note">
<paragraph pageId="36" pageNumber="89">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="37" lastPageNumber="90" pageId="36" pageNumber="89">
This species was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Handlirsch, A" journalOrPublisher="Akademie der Wissenschaften in Wien. Mathematisch-Naturwissenschaftliche Classe. Abtheilung I" pageId="55" pageNumber="108" pagination="657 - 942" refId="B53" refString="Handlirsch, A, 1893. Monographie der mit Nysson und Bembex verwandten Grabwespen. VII. Sitzungsberichte der Kaiserlichen. Akademie der Wissenschaften in Wien. Mathematisch-Naturwissenschaftliche Classe. Abtheilung I: 657 - 942" title="Monographie der mit Nysson und Bembex verwandten Grabwespen. VII. Sitzungsberichte der Kaiserlichen." year="1893">Handlirsch (1893)</bibRefCitation>
from Delagoa Bay (Mozambique). 
<bibRefCitation author="Arnold, G" journalOrPublisher="Annals of the Transvaal Museum" pageId="52" pageNumber="105" pagination="320 - 380" refId="B1" refString="Arnold, G, 1929. The Sphegidae of South Africa. Part 13. Annals of the Transvaal Museum 13: 320 - 380" title="The Sphegidae of South Africa. Part 13." volume="13" year="1929">Arnold (1929)</bibRefCitation>
recorded the species from Delagoa Bay and from four localities 
<pageBreakToken pageId="37" pageNumber="90" start="start">in</pageBreakToken>
Rhodesia (now Zimbabwe): Victoria Falls, Sawmills, Sabyati Valley and Umtali. 
<bibRefCitation author="Parker, JB" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the United States National Museum" pageId="55" pageNumber="108" pagination="1 - 203" publicationUrl="10.5479/si.00963801.75-2776.1" refId="B63" refString="Parker, JB, 1929. A generic revision of the fossorial wasps of the tribes Stizini and Bembicini, with notes and descriptions of new species. Proceedings of the United States National Museum 75: 1 - 203, 10.5479/si.00963801.75-2776.1" title="A generic revision of the fossorial wasps of the tribes Stizini and Bembicini, with notes and descriptions of new species." url="10.5479/si.00963801.75-2776.1" volume="75" year="1929">Parker (1929)</bibRefCitation>
doubtfully referred to this species a specimen labelled &quot;Bosum, 22-4-14, Tessman&quot;. The synonym, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cameron" authorityYear="1910" class="Hexapoda" family="Crabronidae" genus="Bembix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="90" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="testaceicauda">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="90">Bembix testaceicauda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Cameron, P" journalOrPublisher="Annals of the Transvaal Museum" pageId="53" pageNumber="106" pagination="116 - 167" refId="B20" refString="Cameron, P, 1910. On the Aculeate Hymenoptera collected by Mr. A.J.T. Janse, Normal College, Pretoria, in the Transvaal. Annals of the Transvaal Museum 2: 116 - 167" title="On the Aculeate Hymenoptera collected by Mr. A. J. T. Janse, Normal College, Pretoria, in the Transvaal." volume="2" year="1910">Cameron (1910)</bibRefCitation>
from the neighbourhood of Pretoria (Gauteng).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
