<pageBreakToken pageId="38" pageNumber="91" start="start">Geographical</pageBreakToken>
distribution.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="38" pageNumber="91">
A widespread species in northern southern Africa (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Distributions of collection records of Bembix spp.: a Bembix karroensis b Bembix liturata c Bembix loupata d Bembix melanopa e Bembix moebii f Bembix monedula." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11861" pageId="38" pageNumber="91">Fig. 12e</figureCitation>
) northwards to Tanzania and recorded from Ethiopia in northeast Africa but not from northwest Africa.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="38" pageNumber="91" type="floral associations">
<paragraph pageId="38" pageNumber="91">Floral associations.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="38" pageNumber="91">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="91">Unknown</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="38" pageNumber="91" type="nesting">
<paragraph pageId="38" pageNumber="91">Nesting.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="38" pageNumber="91">
Nests in shady situations such as 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“ant-bear”">&quot;ant-bear&quot;</normalizedToken>
holes and sandy ground under dwellings built on piles.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="38" pageNumber="91" type="prey">
